addr="marcelofiore"
title="Marcelo Fiore">Marcelo Fiore</fr:link></fr:contributor></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>We can define a bijective enumeration of the integers by “zigzagging” between the positive and the negative following the pattern<fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (0, -1, 1,-2,2,-3,3,\ldots \right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>:</fr:p><fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[  \begin {aligned}   e&\colon  \mathbb {N}\twoheadrightarrow  \mathbb {Z}\\   e{\mathopen {}\left (i\right )\mathclose {}} &=   \begin {cases}    0 &\text {when } i=0\\    i\div  2 &\text {when } i > 0 \land  2\mid  i\\    -{\mathopen {}\left (i+1\right )\mathclose {}}\div  2 &\text {when } i > 0 \land  \lnot {\mathopen {}\left (2\mid  i\right )\mathclose {}}   \end {cases}  \end {aligned} ]]></fr:tex></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter><fr:tree
